VPN
---

VPN - Virtual Private Network.
Purpose -> safe delivary of data across public network
Working -> VPN  Client installed in the System establishes a VPN Tunnel within the public network which then connects to VPN Server & from there it connects to Company Server.
Benifits -> Anonymity ( hiding my identity -location, IP etc )
            Privacy ( hiding the activity - which websites are visited , what work was done ) 
-: no log policy VPN is more safe

Types of VPN
 1) Site to Site - connects one entire site to another site & is always active.
                  Its ideal when we have multiple remote sites.
                  Its used to connect one Head office to a small branch office.

 2) Remote Access VPN - grants access to a corporate network for only one device.
                      It requires the Host to have an application on its end to connect to corporate network. (eg: cisco anyconnect )

IP sec - used in site to site
TLS - used in remote access - uses port 443.

Full Tunnel -> when connected to VPN , all traffic will be routed to the corpotrate network ( browsing Facebook etc )
Split tunnel -> only the traffic destined to the corporate network is sent over to the VPN , all other traffic is routed as normal.
            Helps in saving bandwidth & provides privacy to users
