-----

CIDR - Classless inter domain routing - it helps in avoiding wastage of IP addresses
Method to allocate IP's . Lower the CIDR range ,higher the IP's available.

In IP V4,  IP adderss consist of total of 32 Bits. ie: 4 octat's

Consider the Notation : 200.10.20.40/28 
                        => 1st 28 bits of the IP belongs to network part & resolve this
28 = Mask / No: of bits representing block/network

network ID part consist of 28 bits  ( 11111111 11111111 11111111 11110000 ) 
Host ID part consist of 4 bits  ( ie: 32 -28 = 4 )
No: of Host = 2^4 -2 = 16 - 2 = 14

