SUBNET 
------
Layer 3 - Network Layer - Router

Subnets breaks large Network to smaller more managable networks.
Helps in minimizing the traffic & organized data flow
Subnet provide direct communication for devices in the same network.

IP address is divided into Network portion & host portion. 
Network admins use subnet mask to identify which part represent Network & the host devices.
Subnet mask for 
Class A -> 255.0.0.0  -> (2 ^ 24 = 16million host)
Class B -> 255.255.0.0 -> ( 2 ^ 16 = 64K host )
Class C -> 255.255.255.0 -> (2 ^ 8 =256 host )

Network ID -> Every Subnet will have its 1st IP starting as Network ID - usually starts with .0 
Broadcast ID -> last IP of subnet range . Its used to talk to all other host within that NW. Ends with no: of host + 1
