HUB 
Purpose - to connect all network devices to an internal network. 
It accepts ethrenet connections from multiple devices.
Its considered as non intelligent edvice bcz it has no idea about where the data is to be sent exactly. 
Data will be sent to all the devices insted of sending it to the target device only. This creates security concerns & unnecessary traffic & it wastes bandwidth 

SWITCH 
Work on Layer 2 of the OSI model ( data link layer ).
layer 2 Works with MAC ( Media Access Control) addresss - > Physical address
switch is similar to hub & it accepts ethernet connections from network devices
Switch is intellegent -it can learn the phycical addresse of the devices connected to it & stores these addresses called MAC addresses in a table. 
So, when a  data packet is sent to a switch ,its only directed to the intended destination port.

HUB & SWITCH is used to exchange data with in LAN. Not used to exchange data outside their network. 
Hub & switch do not read IP address. 

Hub & Switch is used to create networks and Router is used to connect networks
Router - forwards data from one network to another based on IP address. Its the gateway of a network. 


